  - `docs/reference/ti-hotelplanner-implementation-notes.md`
- Lodging implementation prompt set lives in:
  - `docs/prompts/ti-lodging-provider-integration-v2.md`
  - `docs/prompts/ti-lodging-provider-integration-v2-spec.md`
  - `docs/prompts/ti-lodging-provider-integration-v2-engineering.md`
  - `docs/prompts/ti-lodging-provider-qa-checklist-v2.md`
- Database foundation is already present:
  - `supabase/migrations/20260515_ti_weekend_plans_lodging_v1.sql`
- Playwright scaffold exists for future smoke checks:
  - `tests/smoke/ti-weekend-plan-lodging.spec.ts`
- Implementation prompt is currently **ready for execution** after the last feedback pass:
  - provider auth/signature, HotelPlanner endpoint mapping, no-TI checkout, and source fallback requirements are explicit.
- Outstanding for implementation handoff:
  - Execute the docs as one build run and run the lodging QA checklist end-to-end.

### Implementation worklist (ordered)
- [x] Add provider abstraction and HotelPlanner client under `apps/ti-web/lib/lodging`.
- [x] Implement `POST /api/lodging/search` with request validation, date/venue fallbacks, rate limit, provider call, and `fallback` response.
- [x] Add `supabase/migrations/20260629_lodging_search_session.sql` with endpoint+IP+UA rate-limit indexing.
- [ ] Implement `/api/lodging/availability`, `/api/lodging/group-request`, `/api/lodging/checkout-handoff`, `/api/lodging/report-sync`.
- [ ] Wire map page props (`tournament_start_date` / `tournament_end_date`) into lodging search input.
- [ ] Add `lodging_search_session` / `lodging_partner_events` persistence and write helpers.
- [ ] Implement event taxonomy tracking and analytics allowlist updates.
- [ ] Add front-end lodging cards/panel via a dedicated component in tournament map flow.
- [ ] Preserve existing Booking.com + VRBO behaviors and no checkout/payment collection in TI.

### UAT to run for this implementation
- [ ] Search and map wiring:
  - Tournament map view can request lodging with mapped `start_date`/`end_date`.
  - Missing dates or missing venue coordinates returns `fallback` state (no blank map).
- [ ] URL handoff integrity (provider fallback):
  - `/go/hotels` builds a HotelPlanner redirect URL with:
    - `destination` and `city` populated from venue context,
    - `sc=`, `source=`, `kw=`, `jobCode=`, and `Custom1-8=` values when passed through.
    - `CheckIn` / `CheckOut` in `mm/dd/yyyy` plus lowercase `checkin` / `checkout` compatibility fields.
  - Confirm click lands on a destination-aware, non-generic white-label HotelPlanner page for a real venue URL.
- [ ] Hotel card rendering:
  - Hotel card displays name, distance, rating/review count, thumbnail, and from-price.
  - Map markers/cards load only after successful API response.
- [ ] Booking flow:
  - Hotel card click fetches availability before showing room details.
  - HotelPlanner white-label handoff opens via POST form (`bundle`) and no payment data is collected by TI.
- [ ] Group request path:
  - “Need 5+ rooms?” CTA opens flow and enforces required group-request fields.
  - `groupTypeCode` defaults/flows consistently (target 143 unless override is intentional).
- [ ] Guardrails:
  - Credentials remain server-side.
  - `reserve` is never surfaced or invoked.
  - Existing `/go/hotels` + `/go/vrbo` redirect/CTA behavior remains intact.

### Step 1 UAT status

- [x] `POST /api/lodging/search` route compiles and runs with provider wiring:
  - `npx tsc -p apps/ti-web/tsconfig.json --noEmit`
  - `node --import tsx apps/ti-web/lib/lodging/hotelPlannerProvider.test.ts`
